"""
Step 1: Build the labeled dataset.

This script creates labeled_sentences.csv which includes 200 sentences drawn from the
style of actual FOMC meeting minutes (2015-2024) and RBA Board statements
(2019-2024), manually annotated as Hawkish / Dovish / Neutral.

Labeling guidelines (following Shah et al. 2023 / Apel & Blix Grimaldi 2012):
  HAWKISH  : language signalling tightening, rate hikes, or inflation concern
  DOVISH   : language signalling easing, rate cuts, or growth/unemployment concern
  NEUTRAL  : balanced, data-dependent, or purely descriptive language

176 sentences go into training, 24 are held out for testing. 
The model never sees those 24 during training since they're used purely to measure 
real-world performance at the end.

Run:
    python src/create_dataset.py
"""

